Brook was looking for the finish but Dan managed to weather the storm at the opening of the round – and somehow fought back. The Brook attack was relentless and Dan reeled around the ring like a drunk, yet still made it to the end of another three minutes of hell.

Brook's red shorts covered that wound on his left leg but there was no hiding place for his challenger.

Dan was taking right hands to the head as if by habit and he went down for the third time from an accumulation of blows. Make that a fourth, Dan falling a split second before the bell.

American referee Earl Brown completed the statutory eight count before agreeing with the challenger's corner that enough was enough.

 

